data.enText: the day of the week after Tuesday and before Thursday

data.text: To see how Wednesday is used, look at the examples at Monday .
Wednesday的用法见词条Monday下的示例。

data.enText: Originally translated from the Latin for ‘day of Mercury’ Mercurii dies and named after the Germanic god Odin .
data.chText: 译自拉丁文Mercurii dies，原意为day of Mercury（水星日），以日耳曼神Odin（奥丁）命名。

example.ex: Come and have supper with us on Wednesday, if you're free...
example.tran: 如果你有空的话，周三晚上来和我们一起吃晚饭吧。

example.ex: Did you happen to see her leave last Wednesday?...
example.tran: 上周三你有没有碰巧看见她离开？

example.ex: David always collects Alistair from school on Wednesdays.
example.tran: 戴维总是在星期三接阿利斯泰尔放学。

value.def: Wednesday is the day after Tuesday and before Thursday.

trans: 圣灰星期三(基督教四旬期首日)
